parameters: ...Phew...\n< Serena >

Yo. Enjoying yourself today? Spread that ass wide
open.\n< Head Clerk >
This is gonna start another rumor for sure.\n< Head Clerk >
I don't care. Just remember our promise.\n< Serena >

You sure are something, Madam. Letting a caged
bird fly free like that...\n< Head Clerk >

I won't run away. I'll definitely repay the
borrowed money.\n< Serena >
That's exactly why I'm going to the guild.\n< Serena >
...Hey, hey, now? After dancing all night long?\n< Head Clerk >
It's not a problem. Time is of the essence.\n< Serena >

...Well, I won't stop you. The key's been left
open. Just go on out.\n< Head Clerk >
But you know, there's work again tonight.\n< Head Clerk >
...It's not a problem.\n< Serena >
Youth is enviable, isn't it?\n< Head Clerk >
Mmm...\n< Serena >

Sigh... I can't even begin to understand how
things ended up like this...\n< Serena >
But today is indeed the promised due date.\n< Serena >

The informant should report the clues about the
Splendorle...\n< Serena >

For that purpose, I paid 250G... 25,000S. Even
borrowing 5,000S to do so.\n< Serena >

It's been tough, but... today everything will be
rewarded. Let's go meet the informant at the
guild.\n< Serena >
It's the building just south of here.\n< Serena >

events.name: 第二部ストーリー　シシリア

parameters: ストーリー　シシリア

Hey, you're dancing pretty sharply today. I was
surprised when I heard you were going out for the
night.\n< Deacon >

With that huge belly of yours, it's impressive how
beautifully you dance.\n< Deacon >

The customers are non-stop. I can sort of
understand why Madam lets you do as you please.\n< Deacon >
It's not like I can act freely...\n< Serena >

My not showing my face for a day must have been
convenient. To make them anxious and drive up the
price... probably.\n< Serena >
Madam is really too soft on you, huh.\n< Deacon >

It's all calculated, I'm sure. My not showing my
face for a day was just right. To make them
anxious and drive up the price... probably.\n< Serena >
Heh, yeah, that might be true.\n< Deacon >

Alright. That's it for the dancing. From the next
hour, you'll be entertaining guests.\n< Deacon >
Understood. I'll go right away.\n< Serena >

Oh? You're not against it? Usually, you have a
face like you stepped in shit.\n< Deacon >
I'm desperate too.\n< Serena >

Oh. Did getting your ass kicked by Madam motivate
you? Good, good...\n< Deacon >

Then, with the next guest, you'll go straight
upstairs. You know what that means?\n< Deacon >
...\n< Serena >

Madam says not to worry because it's not a
customer who'll do anything crazy.\n< Deacon >
...As if I could feel safe...\n< Serena >

...Understood. It's not like I can refuse
anyway...\n< Serena >

Heh heh. That's a good look for you. All gloomy
and resigned, you've learned to fawn, just like a
proper whore.\n< Deacon >
